The paper deals with generating networks of journal relationships from citation and download data, and determining journal impact rankings from these networks using social network centrality metrics. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SD), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, since the paper primarily deals with the analysis of journal impact, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
